{"image_id": "PMC6072022_5", "image_size": [773, 1000], "ocr": [{"text": "Use of long-acting antipsychotics under ordinary practice", "bbox": [481.3, 50.5, 727.4, 60.6]}, {"text": "Table 1. Socio-demographic features.", "bbox": [252.5, 97.5, 409.7, 107.6]}, {"text": "Variables All LAIs, n = 451", "bbox": [252.5, 116.0, 588.4, 126.1]}, {"text": "Age, mean (sd) 41.8 (13.4)", "bbox": [252.5, 132.1, 556.9, 142.2]}, {"text": "Age categories, n (%)", "bbox": [252.5, 147.9, 338.3, 158.0]}, {"text": "18–30 111 (24.6)", "bbox": [481.2, 163.6, 554.6, 173.7]}, {"text": "31–45 161 (35.7)", "bbox": [481.2, 179.5, 554.6, 189.6]}, {"text": "46–60 144 (31.9)", "bbox": [481.2, 195.2, 554.6, 205.3]}, {"text": ">61 35 (7.8)", "bbox": [488.4, 210.9, 544.9, 221.1]}, {"text": "Female, n (%) 177 (39.2)", "bbox": [252.5, 226.8, 554.6, 236.9]}, {"text": "Italian, n (%) 390 (88.2)", "bbox": [252.5, 242.5, 554.6, 252.6]}, {"text": "Housing conditions, n (%)", "bbox": [252.5, 258.4, 360.1, 268.5]}, {"text": "Alone 100 (22.2)", "bbox": [481.4, 274.1, 554.6, 284.2]}, {"text": "With partner and/or children 95 (21.1)", "bbox": [386.4, 289.9, 549.7, 300.0]}, {"text": "With other relatives 229 (50.8)", "bbox": [425.3, 305.7, 554.6, 315.8]}, {"text": "Any residential home 27 (6)", "bbox": [418.6, 321.5, 537.7, 331.6]}, {"text": "Marital status, n (%)", "bbox": [252.5, 337.2, 335.0, 347.3]}, {"text": "Non-conjugated 383 (85.1)", "bbox": [439.3, 353.1, 554.6, 363.2]}, {"text": "Conjugated 67 (14.9)", "bbox": [458.6, 368.8, 549.7, 378.9]}, {"text": "Educational level, n (%)", "bbox": [252.5, 384.6, 348.7, 394.7]}, {"text": "Illiterate/no title 7 (1.6)", "bbox": [439.7, 400.4, 540.1, 410.5]}, {"text": "Primary school 27 (6.1)", "bbox": [444.1, 416.2, 544.9, 426.3]}, {"text": "Secondary school 189 (42.5)", "bbox": [435.1, 431.9, 554.6, 442.0]}, {"text": "Diploma 178 (40)", "bbox": [470.1, 447.8, 547.5, 457.9]}, {"text": "University degree 44 (9.9)", "bbox": [434.3, 463.5, 544.9, 473.6]}, {"text": "Work, n (%)", "bbox": [252.5, 479.3, 303.4, 489.4]}, {"text": "Employed 100 (22.2)", "bbox": [464.6, 495.1, 554.6, 505.2]}, {"text": "Unemployed 221 (49)", "bbox": [453.0, 510.9, 547.5, 521.0]}, {"text": "Student 15 (3.3)", "bbox": [474.4, 526.6, 544.9, 536.7]}, {"text": "Retired 68 (15.1)", "bbox": [476.0, 542.5, 549.7, 552.6]}, {"text": "Housewife/other 47 (10.4)", "bbox": [437.7, 558.2, 549.7, 568.3]}, {"text": "LAI = long-acting injection; n = number of patients; sd = standard deviation", "bbox": [252.5, 581.9, 561.3, 592.0]}, {"text": "https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0201371.t001", "bbox": [252.5, 604.0, 443.1, 614.6]}, {"text": "younger age (OR 0.97; 95% CI 0.95 to 0.98); being employed (OR 2.01; 95% CI 1.14 to 3.56);", "bbox": [252.5, 633.8, 712.6, 646.4]}, {"text": "having a higher score on the BPRS affective subscale (OR 1.09; 95% CI 1.04 to 1.14); and hav-", "bbox": [252.5, 650.2, 718.7, 662.9]}, {"text": "ing a lower number of LAIs prescribed in the past (OR 0.69; 95% CI 0.52 to 0.93). In addition,", "bbox": [252.5, 666.6, 721.6, 679.2]}, {"text": "having a diagnosis other than schizophrenia spectrum and bipolar disorder reduced the proba-", "bbox": [252.5, 683.0, 727.2, 695.6]}, {"text": "bility of receiving SGA LAIs (OR 0.28; 95% CI 0.13 to 0.60).", "bbox": [252.5, 699.5, 551.4, 712.1]}, {"text": "The goodness-of-fit statistics indicated a moderate relationship between the type of LAIs", "bbox": [267.6, 715.9, 710.8, 728.5]}, {"text": "prescribed and the explanatory variables in both models: McKelvey and Zavoina Pseudo-R2", "bbox": [252.5, 729.8, 711.2, 744.9]}, {"text": "explained 18% and 16% of the variability. In calibration view, the models correctly classified", "bbox": [252.5, 748.7, 712.2, 761.3]}, {"text": "73% and 72% of the patients; the p-values associated with Hosmer–Lemeshow statistics were", "bbox": [252.5, 765.1, 715.7, 777.7]}, {"text": "low even though not significant, confirming moderate agreements between predicted proba-", "bbox": [252.5, 781.5, 716.4, 794.1]}, {"text": "bilities and observed data. Finally, the comparison between the BIC values showed a substan-", "bbox": [252.5, 797.9, 718.4, 810.5]}, {"text": "tial difference (25.84), preferring the final model.", "bbox": [252.5, 814.4, 497.6, 827.0]}, {"text": "Discussion", "bbox": [252.5, 845.5, 332.8, 860.7]}, {"text": "In general, present data confirm the expectation that a broader spectrum of individuals is cur-", "bbox": [252.5, 869.3, 722.6, 882.0]}, {"text": "rently prescribed LAIs as compared to the past. A wide range of socio-demographic and", "bbox": [252.5, 885.7, 692.7, 898.4]}, {"text": "PLOS ONE | https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0201371 August 2, 2018 6 / 17", "bbox": [45.5, 946.7, 727.3, 956.8]}]}